fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.design

Interface IPageSelector


  • @PluginService
public interface IPageSelector
    Provides custom page selection rules, overriding default page selection rules.

    Thread safety: implementations are required to be immutable and therefore completely thread-safe.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies

    • Method Detail

      • selectDashboardPage

        default IDashboardPage selectDashboardPage(IDashboardPage page,
                                           ITicket usingTicket)
        Selects the dashboard page for an authenticated user.

        The preselected page (either selected using the default ranking algorithm, or by another page selector with higher precedence) is passed as a parameter, and can either be returned as-is, or overridden.

        Note: the page context must not be set on returned instances when this method returns.

        Parameters:
        page - the preselected page, or null if none.
        usingTicket - the ticket authenticating the user requesting the page.
        Returns:
        the page passed as a parameter (if the default selection does not need overridden), or an overriding implementation that returns appropriate values for specific properties of the page, and delegates all other properties to the page that was passed as a parameter.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        IDesignService.getDashboard(ITicket)

      • selectCreateFormPage

        default IFormPage selectCreateFormPage(IFormPage page,
                                       ITicket usingTicket,
                                       ISource forSource)
        Selects the form page for creating a new item for a specific source.

        The preselected page (either selected using the default ranking algorithm, or by another page selector with higher precedence) is passed as a parameter, and can either be returned as-is, or overridden.

        Note: the page context must not be set on returned instances when this method returns.

        Parameters:
        page - the preselected page, or null if none.
        usingTicket - the ticket authenticating the user requesting the page.
        forSource - the source for which the item creation form is to be rendered using the selected page design.
        Returns:
        the page passed as a parameter (if the default selection does not need overridden), or an overriding implementation that returns appropriate values for specific properties of the page, and delegates all other properties to the page that was passed as a parameter.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        IDesignService.getCreateFormPage(ITicket, ISource)

      • selectUpdateFormPage

        default IFormPage selectUpdateFormPage(IFormPage page,
                                       ITicket usingTicket,
                                       IKey forKey)
        Selects the form page for viewing and/or updating a specific item.

        The preselected page (either selected using the default ranking algorithm, or by another page selector with higher precedence) is passed as a parameter, and can either be returned as-is, or overridden.

        Note: the page context must not be set on returned instances when this method returns.

        Parameters:
        page - the preselected page, or null if none.
        usingTicket - the ticket authenticating the user requesting the page.
        forKey - the item to be rendered using the selected page design. The key can be either fetched or unfetched.
        Returns:
        the page passed as a parameter (if the default selection does not need overridden), or an overriding implementation that returns appropriate values for specific properties of the page, and delegates all other properties to the page that was passed as a parameter.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        IDesignService.getUpdateFormPage(ITicket, IKey), IFormPage.adapt(java.util.EnumSet)

      • selectListPage

        default IListPage selectListPage(IListPage page,
                                 IListView forListView)
        Selects the list page for a specific list view. The list view provides access to the user via the associated ticket.

        The preselected page (either selected using the default ranking algorithm, or by another page selector with higher precedence) is passed as a parameter, and can either be returned as-is, or overridden.

        Note: the page context must not be set on returned instances when this method returns.

        Parameters:
        page - the preselected page, or null if none.
        forListView - the list view to be rendered using the selected page design.
        Returns:
        the page passed as a parameter (if the default selection does not need overridden), or an overriding implementation that returns appropriate values for specific properties of the page, and delegates all other properties to the page that was passed as a parameter.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        IDesignService.getListPage(IListView), IListPage.adapt(fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.data.filter.IFilter, fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.data.sort.ISort, java.util.SortedSet, int, int), IListPage.adapt(String, int)

      • selectListPages

        default List<IListPage> selectListPages(List<IListPage> pages,
                                        ITicket usingTicket)
        Selects a collection of list pages for the user authenticated with the specified ticket.

        The preselected pages (either selected using the default ranking algorithm, or by another page selector with higher precedence) is passed as a parameter, and can either be returned as-is, or overridden.

        Note: the page context must not be set on returned instances when this method returns.

        Parameters:
        pages - the collection of preselected pages, or an empty list.
        usingTicket - the ticket providing access to the authenticated user.
        Returns:
        the collection of pages passed as a parameter (if the default selection does not need overridden), or an alternative collection that can change the contents of the collection passed as a parameter (where changes can include adding and removing elements, or even substituting elements with overriding implementations).
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        IDesignService.getListPages(ITicket), IDesignService.getListPages(ITicket, fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.connector.IPlatformConnector)
